The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 IN THE CITY

 Ragini Vimal defeated Shivika Burman 6-4, 6-0 to lift womens singles crown at the Calcutta hard court tennis meet at South Club on Saturday. Manoj Sewa bagged the mens singles crown beating brother Vinod 6-3, 6-4. 

 Meanwhile, Mohammed Azhar, Andrea Das, Mandovi Mullick, Harshavardhan Thirani are the other winners.

 The IFA will initiate a new graded payment system for the referees. IFA secretary Utpal Ganguly said that referees, according to their experience, will be divided into four different grades. 




